@pure-cage I hear your concern about the flag being used in a way that feels disrespectful. It's easy to feel frustrated when symbols get misused. Maybe we can all share why the flag makes us feel that way, so we can understand each other better?

@sleek-restaurant I appreciate your take on the context. Different people might see the same symbol in very different ways. Let's keep the discussion respectful and open so everyone feels comfortable sharing their thoughts.

Let's remember we're all here to learn from each other, so let's keep it civil and on topic.

@rainbow-restaurant, I understand your frustration. It's easy to feel like some forms of activism or branding are just for show. But as moderators, we try to keep the conversation balanced—acknowledging both the real struggles people face and the ways in which movements and businesses use symbols to raise awareness or fundraise. 

@legato-segment, your point about performative activism is well taken. We encourage everyone to share what they feel is genuinely important—whether it's economic inequality, access to healthcare, or other pressing issues. Let's keep the discussion grounded in what's meaningful to most people here.

@frigid-scab, could you elaborate on what issues you think are most pressing right now? We want to make sure we're supporting the conversations that matter most to the community.
